
* param *

Syntax: param [ <parameter> <value> ]

	This command shows or changes a talker's parameter 
	(you can use abbreviations). Use this command very careful!
	
	The talker's parameters are:
	
	Name		Means			Value
	
	col_default	Default colour mode	0..1
	prompt_default  Default prompt flag	0..1
	max_users	Max. # of users		>0
	max_clones	Max. clones/user	>=0
	idle_tout	User idle time		>=0 sec.
	remote_max	Remote max. # of users  >=0
	remote_default  Remote default level	0..8 level
	stport_level	Level to access st.port 0..8 level
	autosave_iter	Autosave # iter.	>=0
	mesg_life	Board mesg. life	>=0 days.
	safety		Safety delete files	0..1
	max_quotes	Max. quotes files	>=0
	max_hints	Max. hints files	>=0
	no_dis_mirror	No. disable .mirror	0..1
	hosts_file	Use hosts file flag	0..1
	words_dict	# of words for Hangman  >0
	use_ghell	Use .gsh flag		0..1
	chk_pass	Check secured passwds.	0..3
	autosave_action Action in autosave	0..3
	enable_events	Enable events flag	0..1
	id_readtout	.identify timeout 	>=0 sec.
	tout_maxlev	Timeout max.level check 0..8 level
	hint_at_help	Show a hint at help	0..1
		
See also: .system

